DefaultMessage.SourceString: If it isn't  <enemy>Slone's newest lapdog.</> That  <enemy>warmongering charlatan</> figured me out, huh?
Whoa. Like, DOOM doom?
No... She didn't... Excuse me. I have to make a call.
Yeah, yeah. Whatever, kid.
"Impending doom?" Please. Slone doesn't stand a chance.
I'll collect fresh samples right away.
We must protect the biodiversity of the swamp.
Roger that. When the time comes, I'll proceed to the rendezvous point.
Roger. Mission is a go.
I'm all for bootin' those invaders, but...
My corn! My precious corn!!
So I should run away? You think I'm a coward, mate?!
Where's your fightin' spirit?!
So Slone's ending the world, huh? Can't say I'm surprised.
But I'm definitely a little jealous.
Wow. I'd better move my cache of Meowscles Morsels.
Well <enemy>I'm done</> designing inelegant tools of war. There's a whole world out there to study.
The Aliens care about science, and math, and... well, yeah,  <enemy>destruction.</>
Thank you. You will be rewarded handsomely for your betrayal.
Is that so? Hmm.
But <b>I can convince them</> to save this world. Continue my meaningful work.
My father built that ship! No one would dare attack it!
Ha, you mean that big ship up there?
Sounds chaotic. I'm in.
I just need to  <enemy>get you out of my way.</>
Uhh... Are we sure we want that big thing in the sky to end up here on the ground?
You know... Where people live?
Slone's done it now. That's not gonna end well.
I'll warn all the butterflies right away.
So that's why Slone was asking me about my explosives designs.
I've got to warn everyone. Quickly.
Nice try. I've got three days left on this trip.
What part of "out of office" don't you understand?!
Don't worry about me. I've got a getaway driver.
